Rules to Remember:
The number of columns in INSERT INTO and SELECT must be the same
The column order must match
The SELECT statement can include:
Table columns
NULL values
Fixed values (e.g., 'Unknown')
Expressions


INSERT INTO persons (id, person_name, birth_date, phone)
SELECT
    id,
    first_name,
    NULL,
    'Unknown'
FROM customers;


Explanation
customers → source table
persons → target table
id is inserted into id
first_name is inserted into person_name
birth_date is set to NULL
phone is set to 'Unknown'
